Test: Two-Variable Linear Regression - EqParse

Ivan Jacob Agaloos Pesigan

2021-02-20

Source: vignettes/tests/test_two-variable-regression-EqParse.Rmd
test_two-variable-regression-EqParse.Rmd
eq <- "
  # lhs op   rhs par.label par.start
    e   by   y   1         NA
    y   on   x   beta      0.00
    e   with e   sigmae2   1.25
    x   with x   sigmax2   0.25
    y   on   1   alpha     0.00
    x   on   1   mux       0.50
"
ramR:::EqParse(eq)
#>   lhs   op rhs par.label par.index par.names par.start par.free
#> 1   e   by   y         1         1      <NA>        NA    FALSE
#> 2   y   on   x      beta        p1      beta      0.00     TRUE
#> 3   e with   e   sigmae2        p2   sigmae2      1.25     TRUE
#> 4   x with   x   sigmax2        p3   sigmax2      0.25     TRUE
#> 5   y   on   1     alpha        p4     alpha      0.00     TRUE
#> 6   x   on   1       mux        p5       mux      0.50     TRUE
eq <- "
  # lhs op   rhs value
    e   by   y   1
    y   on   x   1
    e   with e   1
    x   with x   0.25
    y   on   1   0
    x   on   1   0.50
"
ramR:::EqParse(eq)
#>   lhs   op rhs par.label par.index par.names
#> 1   e   by   y      1.00      1.00        NA
#> 2   y   on   x      1.00      1.00        NA
#> 3   e with   e      1.00      1.00        NA
#> 4   x with   x      0.25      0.25        NA
#> 5   y   on   1      0.00      0.00        NA
#> 6   x   on   1      0.50      0.50        NA
# equality constraint
# starting values should be identical
# for parameters constrained to be equal
eq <- "
  # lhs op   rhs par.label par.start
    e   by   y   1         NA
    y   on   x   beta      0.00
    e   with e   sigmax2   1.25
    x   with x   sigmax2   1.25
    y   on   1   alpha     0.00
    x   on   1   mux       0.50
"
ramR:::EqParse(eq)
#>   lhs   op rhs par.label par.index par.names par.start par.free
#> 1   e   by   y         1         1      <NA>        NA    FALSE
#> 2   y   on   x      beta        p1      beta      0.00     TRUE
#> 3   e with   e   sigmax2        p2   sigmax2      1.25     TRUE
#> 4   x with   x   sigmax2        p2   sigmax2      1.25     TRUE
#> 5   y   on   1     alpha        p3     alpha      0.00     TRUE
#> 6   x   on   1       mux        p4       mux      0.50     TRUE
# `\n` and `;` as line breaks
eq <- "
    e   by   y   1       NA ; y   on   x   beta    0.00 ;
    e   with e   sigmae2 1.25 ; x   with x   sigmax2 0.25 ;
    y   on   1   alpha   0.00 \n x   on   1   mux     0.50 ;
"
ramR:::EqParse(eq)
#>   lhs   op rhs par.label par.index par.names par.start par.free
#> 1   e   by   y         1         1      <NA>        NA    FALSE
#> 2   y   on   x      beta        p1      beta      0.00     TRUE
#> 3   e with   e   sigmae2        p2   sigmae2      1.25     TRUE
#> 4   x with   x   sigmax2        p3   sigmax2      0.25     TRUE
#> 5   y   on   1     alpha        p4     alpha      0.00     TRUE
#> 6   x   on   1       mux        p5       mux      0.50     TRUE
eq <- "
  # lhs op   rhs par.label par.start
    e   by   y
    y   on   x   beta      0.00
    e   with e   sigmax2   1.25
    x   with x   sigmax2   1.25
    y   on   1   alpha     0.00
    x   on   1   mux       0.50
"
testthat::test_that("incomplete eq - trigger warning in do.call rbind", {
  testthat::expect_error(
    ramR:::EqParse(eq)
  )
})
#> Test passed ðŸ¥‡
